headline: Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang Pushes Back On Fears Surrounding Big Tech's $700 Billion CapEx Surge: 'Compute Equals Revenues' In The New AI World
summary: Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang said he is confident Big Tech's nearly $700 billion AI capital spending boom will continue as "compute equals revenues," highlighting strong demand visibility into 2027 alongside the company's 73% revenue surge and upbeat first-quarter outlook.

headline: Alphabet Energy Deals Shape Long Term AI Data Center Outlook
summary: Alphabet, parent of Google (NasdaqGS:GOOGL), has entered into major energy deals with Xcel Energy in Minnesota and AES Corporation in Texas to supply new data centers with large-scale clean power. The partnerships include plans for what is described as the world's largest iron air battery system and multi decade energy infrastructure commitments tied to Google's facilities.
